23. Merge k Sorted Lists
題目
Merge k sorted linked lists and return it as one sorted list. Analyze and describe its complexity.
Example:
Input:
[
  1->4->5,
  1->3->4,
  2->6
]
Output: 1->1->2->3->4->4->5->6
思路 - priority queue
這題比較簡單的做法就是使用 priority queue 來儲放 k 個節點。

將 k 個最前面的節點，丟至 priority queue 中。
從 pq 中取出最小的節點 current
串到 result 節點
將 current->next 節點丟到 pq。
repeat。

Runtime: 24 ms, faster than 98.48% of C++ online submissions for Merge k Sorted Lists.
Memory Usage: 11.3 MB, less than 68.54% of C++ online submissions for Merge k Sorted Lists.
/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * struct ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode *next;
 *     ListNode(int x) : val(x), next(NULL) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
private:
    struct compare{
        bool operator()(ListNode* p, ListNode* q){
            // 小 -> 大
            return p->val > q->val;
        }
    };

public:
    ListNode* mergeKLists(vector& lists) {
        priority_queue, compare> pq;
        ListNode* dummy = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode* head = dummy;

        for (int i=0; i  0){
            ListNode* cur = pq.top();
            head->next = cur;
            pq.pop();
            head = head->next;

            if(cur->next){
                pq.push(cur->next);
            }
        }

        return dummy->next;
    }
};

